There is something specifically grotesque about the apostles in Berserk that appear during the Eclipse scene, the ones in the rest of the story are better thought out and designed with a particular vision, e.g. this one is like an evil vampire thing, that one is snake demon, etc.

A monster that tells a story like "fat creature with big mouth, signifying gluttony" can never be that horrible, it has a sense to it. But illogical designs of just bloated red bodies with heads under their armpits and arms out of their temples are pure chaos, pure monstrosity.
